data.title: Evangelos Venizelos – POLITICO
data.meta_description: Latest news from POLITICO about Evangelos Venizelos
data.text:
Turkey urged to stop challenging Cyprus’s energy plans

Increased tensions between Turkey and Cyprus discussed at first trilateral meeting of leaders of Cyprus, Greece and Egypt.

Greece’s government wins confidence vote

The result may silence calls for early elections for now, but opinion polls show public support is still shifting towards the far left.

Greece claims ‘ultimately successful’ presidency of the EU’s Council of Ministers

Greece has emerged stronger from its six months holding the rotating presidency of the EU’s Council of Ministers, but has failed to put forward creative ideas about the Union’s migration policy.

Greece’s new ministers sworn in

Samaras brings in economist as finance minister in response to poor performance in European elections.

Greek ministers to change posts

Coalition partners exclude early national elections after poor result in European Parliament elections.

Greek government announces cabinet reshuffle

Ministerial posts will be changed but coalition partners exclude early national elections following their poor performance in the European Parliament elections.

A Greek ‘referendum’ on austerity

Far-left and far-right are hoping for major gains, while the ruling New Democracy says that its austerity measures are working.

Local elections biggest test for Samaras

Samaras’ government party Néa Dimokratía tied with far-left opposition party Syriza in first round of local Greek elections.

Greece seeks enhanced co-operation on financial transaction tax

France and Germany have renewed their efforts to clinch a deal on a financial transaction tax, aiming to agree a joint position at a Franco-German ministerial summit in Paris on 19 February.

Talks with Greece awkwardly timed

Scrutiny coincides with Council presidency.

Crisis? What crisis?

Government upbeat about financial future
